main event: On September 5, 1956, in Concord, New Hampshire, a civilian reported observing three unidentified flying objects (UFOs) moving upward at a fast speed.
interesting points: Conflicting data was noted, with the possibility of the object being a balloon due to its upward motion, but no substantiating data was available.
The objects were described as bright lights, almost stationary, and approximately 25 seconds in duration at a range of 6 miles.
The report lasted for one hour, and it was a ground-visual observation made at night.
No physical evidence or photographs were documented in the report.
The source of the observation was a civilian, adding to the credibility of the report.
sighted object: three bright lights moving rapidly upward
